# Title Case (mandatory on user-facing UI)

The owner requires **Title Case** on headings (h1–h6), table headers (th), buttons, labels, nav links, and section titles on diligence and staff-facing pages.

## How it works

- **Runtime:** `js/ui-title-case.js` applies MediForge title case when the page loads.
- **Every diligence HTML page** must include:
  `<script src="/js/ui-title-case.js" defer></script>`
- **Do not** use CSS `text-transform: uppercase` on headings or form labels.

## Diligence pages (all required)

`/ontario-readiness`, `/strategic-partner-letter`, `/term-sheet`, `/valuation-equity-structure`, `/project-plan`, `/revenue-projection`, `/financial-model`, `/capital-deployment-detail`, `/capabilities`, `/evidence-binder`, `/ontario-self-assessment`

## Before you finish

1. New or edited diligence page: add `ui-title-case.js` if missing.
2. Run `npm run check:diligence-title-case` (also in full `npm run check`).
3. Write new headings in Title Case in source when practical (script fixes at render time).

## Never

- Ship a diligence page without `ui-title-case.js`.
- Rely on handover alone: the check script blocks merges/builds if the script tag is missing.

See **`AGENT-HANDOVER.md` Rule #2b**.
